00:40:15.780 --> 00:40:16.780
[audience laughs]

00:40:16.780 --> 00:40:17.780
It's time he learned.

00:40:17.780 --> 00:40:18.780
&gt;&gt;Older Male: That doesn't work.

00:40:18.780 --> 00:40:19.780
[audience laughs]

00:40:19.780 --> 00:40:22.240
&gt;&gt;Dave: No, I know. You know what does? I
tell ya. I believe in parenting by embarrassing.

00:40:22.240 --> 00:40:23.279
[audience laughs]

00:40:23.279 --> 00:40:28.710
I, and I-I-I-I've said this for a long time
that the mistake that we make, I, I have two

00:40:28.710 --> 00:40:33.369
kids. This is the mistake you make as a parent,
is you try to get their love and respect,

00:40:33.369 --> 00:40:36.430
and that works great until they reach the
age of 12 or 13 months.

00:40:36.430 --> 00:40:39.009
[audience laughs]

00:40:39.009 --> 00:40:41.452
The sooner they start to tal, they start to
figure out you're a dork. And by the, by the

00:40:41.452 --> 00:40:45.089
time they're 16, you know, they, you're, they
don't want to be, really they don't want anything

00:40:45.089 --> 00:40:49.680
to do with you. However, you develop, you,
at the same time, an incredible power of embarrassment

00:40:49.680 --> 00:40:53.769
over them; it's very strong. And most parents,
its parents are reluctant to use it. They

00:40:53.769 --> 00:40:56.359
think it's bad when they embarrass their children
but it's actually a very effective control

00:40:56.359 --> 00:41:02.119
technique. If you're in a public place with
it, a, an adolescent child, is giving you

00:41:02.119 --> 00:41:04.869
any trouble, just don't say, "You're gonna
be grounded", or something like that, so.

00:41:04.869 --> 00:41:05.869
They ask you

00:41:05.869 --> 00:41:06.869
[sings]

00:41:06.869 --> 00:41:07.869
Well, I was just walkin' down the...

00:41:07.869 --> 00:41:08.869
[talks]

00:41:08.869 --> 00:41:09.869
Sing! sing!

00:41:09.869 --> 00:41:14.729
Boy that will stop them, whatever they're
doing. If you will stop singing, they will

00:41:14.729 --> 00:41:15.790
do anything you want.

00:41:15.790 --> 00:41:16.790
[audience laughs]

00:41:16.790 --> 00:41:24.099
Alright, they will, try that, try the..when
I found this out, my, my son, Rob, he's now;

00:41:24.099 --> 00:41:30.390
he's now 29-years old so I can't really do
these things. But when I learned the power

00:41:30.390 --> 00:41:34.390
of embarrassment, how really strong it was.
He was 13. He was in middle school and I got

00:41:34.390 --> 00:41:38.510
a call at the Miami Herald from the Oscar
Meyer Corporation saying they were bringing

00:41:38.510 --> 00:41:42.720
the Oscar Meyer Weinermobile to Miami. The
Weinermobile, I'm sure you've seen it, it's

00:41:42.720 --> 00:41:47.969
a giant fiberglass hot dog in a bun with a
loudspeaker, this is sound but of course the

00:41:47.969 --> 00:41:52.109
Weinermobile has been here. Everybody comes
to go.. and it, there are actually six Weinermobiles.

00:41:52.109 --> 00:41:55.359
I don't know if you knew that. We, this nation
leads the world--

00:41:55.359 --> 00:41:56.359
[audience laughs]

00:41:56.359 --> 00:42:04.150
in Weinermobile technology. Although, Iran
is developing one. But anyway, they like to

00:42:04.150 --> 00:42:07.619
get publicity for the Weinermobile so they
call me up at the Miami Herald and say, "We're

00:42:07.619 --> 00:42:12.579
bringing the Weinermobile to Miami. Would
you like to drive it for a day?" And I said,

00:42:12.579 --> 00:42:13.579
"Heck yes."

00:42:13.579 --> 00:42:14.579
[audience chuckles]

00:42:14.579 --> 00:42:17.270
I knew exactly what I wanted to do. I wanted
to pick my son up in middle school.

00:42:17.270 --> 00:42:20.510
[audience laughs]

00:42:20.510 --> 00:42:25.630
Because there he is in peer pressure hell,
you don't know. Never forget the moment Rob

00:42:25.630 --> 00:42:29.279
came out of the, of the school, and there's
all these moms in their minivans and looming

00:42:29.279 --> 00:42:31.010
up behind is a really big hot dog--

00:42:31.010 --> 00:42:32.010
[audience laughs]

00:42:32.010 --> 00:42:34.859
with a loudspeaker going, "Rob Barry, please
report to the Weinermobile."

00:42:34.859 --> 00:42:35.859
[audience laughs]

00:42:35.859 --> 00:42:41.130
I'll tell you, if a 13-year old could suffer
a heart attack, he would have. And I know

00:42:41.130 --> 00:42:44.920
what you're thinking, at the end of the day
it was fun for you, but you scarred your child

00:42:44.920 --> 00:42:49.349
psychologically for life. Yes, but it was
worth it.

00:42:49.349 --> 00:42:50.349
[audience laughs]

00:42:50.349 --> 00:42:54.049
Maybe you can get the Weinermobile.

00:42:54.049 --> 00:42:55.049
Yes?

